\begin_layout Subsection
Problem
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The analysis of supply (of products available in the country/region) vs
 the demand (consumption levels) can be used to detect the several class
 of products identified as that for signaling effect.
 A comparison in the spending patterns with the rest of the countries of
 similar economic output can provide insights into stable or transient spending
 patterns.
 The differences in sales and effect of advertising for consumption goods
 vs signaling products is to be used to detect tendencies of signaling.
 A clustering of articles (services or goods) - based on their common purpose
 in respective societies can thus demarcate differences in these trends.
 A key task in this regard is to find out the short-term or seasonal volatility
 of consumption of goods relates with the change in economic variables of
 the countries.
 I suspect that goods that are have emotional (familial) values should vary
 differently from consumption goods.
\end_layout

